{
  "stem": "27770.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Now, you will probably ask what you asked before this question, how come since 1939 when the Jews got taken already in Poland and other countries, and here we are in 1944, and we are so stupid.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we don't know where they're taking us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Hungarian, they used to fight.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In 1940-- 14 until 1918, there was an Austrian Hungarian army.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were officers, Jews, and they were you-- by Franz Joseph, the Jews had a lot of rights, and we had a good time for the Jews.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So these-- the Hungarians, they was hoping, and it was believing that we, who they're fighting in Hungarian army, they do it for the Polish Jews, they do it for the other Jews, but we Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This wouldn't happen.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You understand?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In fact, when the Hungarian, they occupied in 1938, a lot of Jews still were in the Hungarian Army, officers and everything.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So nobody believed it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And a lot of time, people came to tell stories what happened in Poland, and when you don't want to hear it, that story, you don't hear it.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Happened once when Poland already, most of the Jews had taken to Poland, they came some of them who survived, run away, to Munkacs, nobody took them in the house because it was very dangerous.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "If they caught that Polish Jew in your house, next they took away your house, they took away your store, they took away your money, and you had to go to forced labor.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So it was very dangerous.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The way we organized it to help those Jews, we let them each time we left the older synagogues open.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they used to sleep in synagogues and once in a while we threw in food.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I mean, they should survive.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
